  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="NL">ACC Securing Peaceful Elections in Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="NL">The threat of electoral violence and its attendant risks to Ghana&#x2019;s democratic stability, peace and security remain potent and higher in the forth coming December polls.  This  project seeks to ensure that  Presidential Candidates Peace Pact is signed by the leading political parties in Ghana.  Peace Pact have proven to a mechanism for preventing the outbreak of widespread electoral violence in the streets while nudging the contesting candidates towards due processes of judicial adjudication in disputes over official results of presidential elections.  The PCPP aims at committing  the two leading presidential candidates  to work together, before, during and  post-elections, to eradicate electoral violence, impunity and injustice in Ghana&#x2019;s multiparty democracy. The National Chief Imam, the highly revered and loved leader of the Muslim community in Ghana, will be a Co-Convenor, with the National Peace Council (NPC), of the presidential candidates to sign the Elections 2020 Peace Pact.  The event would  take place in Accra not later than in the week of 23rd November 2020.</narrative>
  </description>
